##A total rout of breakups?

Function description, how wonderful, this earthly life.

Material life reference

By Zhao Xiaowei
Source: Material Life Reference (ID: WZSHCK)
01.

On her first day back in Beijing, Wang dug through medicine boxes, drawers and lockers to find more than 40 masks, including two packs of disposable masks, one pack of disposable surgical masks, and several high-end items: N95.

N95 is the previous two years when the smog serious specially bought, other masks, is in the past to buy medicine "make-up goods. ". Like many young people living in the city, Wang's family medicine comes almost exclusively from the Chinese medicine channel in takeout or from the medicine delivery APP. This kind of purchase will usually have set up to send the threshold, more often, Wang Meng is in order to scrape up enough 50 minus 20 type of promotional activities.

No one can think of, then low-cost collection of goods, in this winter, has become a cover hard currency.

Wang Meng has not bought a mask since. Not Anymore, to be exact. She has placed seven or eight orders online, on various shopping platforms, and tried to buy on behalf of trusted bloggers on Weibo, but they were either refunded or have not yet been shipped.

She was grateful for her inadvertent hoarding of survival supplies, but regretted not supporting her family's decision to buy more masks years ago. "At that time, there were already people in the drugstore buying 10 packs and 10 packs. I also told my mother not to stock up and leave it for those who needed it more. " Wang Meng said that the epidemic was not serious at that time, on the one hand, she felt that the people in the affected areas needed it more, and on the other hand, she was very optimistic, after the Spring Festival production capacity comes up, the mask natural enough.

To "atone" for her pollyanna optimism, she sent her parents more than half of her face masks.

In addition to the masks, Wang also found three small bottles of 75 percent alcohol in the closet, two boxes of disposable gloves, two bottles of 84 disinfectant, and a small packet of alcohol cotton pads. Alcohol disinfects toenails before they are medicated for a crush injury, with drugstores charging $10 for a vial and online shopping for six vials of 19; disposable gloves are a testament to that year's love of baking.

The hoarding habit is known on the Internet as "Hamster Disease" , probably because the animal has rolling cheeks and is good for storing food, the German word for "store" being "hamster. ". As a single woman living alone in a big city, Wang Meng has a clear understanding of her hamster nature.

On the one hand, she's hoarding out of a sense of security, and she's always buying an extra set of necessities for a rainy day. On the other hand, she's somewhat fatally attributing it to Taurus, sales Promotion, such as the full reduction campaign, the second zero yuan, buy three free and so on, stimulated her desire to purchase is also a desire to conquer, the intention of careful and merchants battle price, is to stock up more and more.

When this winter comes, it will be eleven and 12 rounds of the important periodic campaign. Therefore, the home of the laundry detergent, disinfectant, toilet paper and even rice grain and oil, are in a saturated state.

In Beijing, a city with relatively complete supplies and relatively quick delivery, such hoarding was not necessary, but after the residential area was closed and express delivery could not enter, the operation of carrying goods by hand from the gate and then climbing up the stairs was carried out, the difficulty of purchasing living materials has skyrocketed.

"My life was given to me by hamster disease, " Wang said, after a month of literally being cooped up at home.

02.

After keeping a "survival guide" to the end of days inventory in his friends' circle, Li Xiao laments that his years of "breaking away" have been spent.

She's a minimalist. Physical Restraint, organized storage, quarterly cleaning and sorting of household items. So, despite having a cat and a husband who loves to buy books and snacks, the environment remains empty and clean as far as the eye can see.

Like many breakaway fans, Li Xiao's primer is Eiko Yamashita's breakaway and Marie Kondo's Jinsei Ga Tokimeku Katadzuke no Mahō, the former about ideas and the latter about practice. After three years, Li Xiao found life refreshing and his desire to shop greatly diminished, "especially suited to the downgrading of consumption. ".

Li Xiao admits that part of his admiration for minimalism and detachment stems from his desire to control life, the need to control quantity in order to have everything sorted and organized, and the harsh reality of living in a cubicle. Whenever and her husband because to throw, to buy a dispute, she will cite the unreasonable price of land inch gold as an argument: We are poor is the money to buy things? You have to calculate how much space it takes!

But she didn't think it would end this time. The first to go is the cat. Years ago she had three bags of cat litter in her house, which was about the limit of what she could store. Did Not expect to endure in February, the cat sand eye looked bottom, but still delivery delivery to the community. Eventually, Li Xiao placed an order at an online supermarket, picked a delivery terminal that was an hour away on the subway, and ventured out four days later.

A bag of cat litter six pounds, the Li Xiao dragged home six bags. After this campaign, she felt physically and mentally under attack, and even moved the "training civet cat toilet with" mind. Another blow is that when buying daily necessities for their parents, jd.com, which has always been reliable, was out of starch. After Taobao placed the order, it took a full two weeks to receive the goods.

And some people don't get out at all. Li Xiao's best friend, Oyasu, whose parents are both in Jingzhou, once faced a food shortage. Finally let the old couple through the most difficult period, is hoarding in the Cabinet of Agaric, flower mushrooms, day lily, sweet potato powder..

Li Xiao was a little afraid: In his own small home, he would have lasted at most a week. After collecting a list of household supplies, she started a shopping list: water purification tablets, high capacity chargers, medical kits, toolkits..

She even found "doomsday food packs" on the Internet sold by Costco in the US, which include a variety of freeze-dried, dehydrated and ready-to-eat foods with a shelf life of between 25 and 30 years. And, of course, the price is good: $6,000 a year for a premium suit.

From one extreme to the other, Li Xiao sees the same inner core: Insecurity, a desire to take control of life more firmly.

"The foundation of 'breaking away' is social security, such as take-out, online shopping, transportation are very convenient, personal capital reserve is relatively sufficient, it is possible to trust to give up. "She says this winter has made her feel that the setting is relatively fragile and that everything that seems convenient doesn't seem so secure.

03.

Zhihu on a recent question is very popular: After this epidemic, you will "break up" it?

Mostly entry-level players who yell "never" at the top of their lungs. The sad stories are all similar: In the midst of a recent, spontaneous breakup, someone threw away a mask, gloves, alcohol, an old raincoat, or a last minute snack, rice, corn oil, and someone cried, just before the Spring Festival threw away the goggles that the doctor gave after myopic operation, "thought that lifetime all did not use! "

Although some masks do go out of date, in a time when masks are in short supply, even after a period of expiration, it's definitely safer than running around naked. So when the "break-away" camp quipped that "those who hoard don't hoard masks" , some hoarders who dug out airline giveaways from the corner protested.

Others cite last year's Marie Kondo Sale, in which the Jinsei Ga Tokimeku Katadzuke no Mahō writer was criticized for selling lifestyle items at exorbitant prices on his website, "Let us throw away 'not heart' things, just to buy her goods? " Netizens to her own query, once rose to the "breakaway" reasonable doubt above. 1

In Japan, the birthplace of the concept of "breaking away from home" , under the influence of rumors that "life paper will be in short supply" , there has been a scramble for toilet paper in many places. Two

The Citadel was falling, but there were still those who struggled to hold high the banner of "parting from one's family" . Liunan District was one of them. In his view, misunderstanding stems from the Chinese People's misunderstanding of the meaning of breaking and parting. "breaking up isn't just throwing, " Liunan District said. "It's more like throwing without purpose or principle, the 'detach' movement is more precise and purposeful: "detach from the unwanted, the unwanted, the unwanted, the clinging. ".

Therefore, how to define "unnecessary" and "redundant" is the crux of the matter. In this dimension, under the epidemic, many people have completed vivid exercises in the unnecessary: meals are abandoned, drinks are abandoned, parties are abandoned, unnecessary small talk is abandoned, and now Liunan District, working from home, finds nothing more relaxing, life doesn't seem to be any different.

Others have taken the opportunity to further jettison some of their circle of friends. "The epidemic is the litmus test, " Liunan District said. "You think you've cleaned up a long time ago, but someone always comes along and tries to push your buttons. "

He even took the opportunity to return a few groups, wechat home page small red circle moment refreshing. "When you handle things, you can take care of them, but you can't be soft on people who don't share the same outlook, " said the high-level "parting" player.

Reference:

1. "35-year-old Japanese "cut off from the Queen" selling goods controversy, by teaching people to throw things to earn 50 million people, " Source: Sina Caijing, January 2,2020;
2. Panic buying of household paper in many parts of Japan, government calls for calm action, source: Chinanews.com, February 28,2020;

She even found "doomsday food packs" on the Internet sold by Costco in the US, which include a variety of freeze-dried, dehydrated and ready-to-eat foods with a shelf life of between 25 and 30 years. And, of course, the price is good: $6,000 a year for a premium suit.

From one extreme to the other, Li Xiao sees the same inner core: Insecurity, a desire to take control of life more firmly.

"The foundation of 'breaking away' is social security, such as take-out, online shopping, transportation are very convenient, personal capital reserve is relatively sufficient, it is possible to trust to give up. "She says this winter has made her feel that the setting is relatively fragile and that everything that seems convenient doesn't seem so secure.

03.

Zhihu on a recent question is very popular: After this epidemic, you will "break up" it?

Mostly entry-level players who yell "never" at the top of their lungs. The sad stories are all similar: In the midst of a recent, spontaneous breakup, someone threw away a mask, gloves, alcohol, an old raincoat, or a last minute snack, rice, corn oil, and someone cried, just before the Spring Festival threw away the goggles that the doctor gave after myopic operation, "thought that lifetime all did not use! "

Although some masks do go out of date, in a time when masks are in short supply, even after a period of expiration, it's definitely safer than running around naked. So when the "break-away" camp quipped that "those who hoard don't hoard masks" , some hoarders who dug out airline giveaways from the corner protested.

Others cite last year's Marie Kondo Sale, in which the Jinsei Ga Tokimeku Katadzuke no Mahō writer was criticized for selling lifestyle items at exorbitant prices on his website, "Let us throw away 'not heart' things, just to buy her goods? " Netizens to her own query, once rose to the "breakaway" reasonable doubt above. 1

In Japan, the birthplace of the concept of "breaking away from home" , under the influence of rumors that "life paper will be in short supply" , there has been a scramble for toilet paper in many places. Two

The Citadel was falling, but there were still those who struggled to hold high the banner of "parting from one's family" . Liunan District was one of them. In his view, misunderstanding stems from the Chinese People's misunderstanding of the meaning of breaking and parting. "breaking up isn't just throwing, " Liunan District said. "It's more like throwing without purpose or principle, the 'detach' movement is more precise and purposeful: "detach from the unwanted, the unwanted, the unwanted, the clinging. ".

Therefore, how to define "unnecessary" and "redundant" is the crux of the matter. In this dimension, under the epidemic, many people have completed vivid exercises in the unnecessary: meals are abandoned, drinks are abandoned, parties are abandoned, unnecessary small talk is abandoned, and now Liunan District, working from home, finds nothing more relaxing, life doesn't seem to be any different.

Others have taken the opportunity to further jettison some of their circle of friends. "The epidemic is the litmus test, " Liunan District said. "You think you've cleaned up a long time ago, but someone always comes along and tries to push your buttons. "

He even took the opportunity to return a few groups, wechat home page small red circle moment refreshing. "When you handle things, you can take care of them, but you can't be soft on people who don't share the same outlook, " said the high-level "parting" player.
